  <!-- ====== FAQ ====== -->
  <section class="lg-section" id="faq" style="background:#fbf6ee;">
    <div class="lg-faq-inner">
      <div class="lg-faq-header">
        <div class="lg-section-eyebrow">Common questions</div>
        <h2 class="lg-section-headline">Things gift-givers <em>ask us.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <details class="lg-faq-item">
        <summary>What if I don't know the baby's name yet?</summary>
        <p class="lg-faq-answer">No problem at all — the recipient picks their own .com when they redeem the code. You don't need to know the name, the spelling, or whether they've decided yet. Many gifts are bought before the shower, sometimes before the parents have settled on a name.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="lg-faq-item">
        <summary>Can I make sure they get this on the day of the shower?</summary>
        <p class="lg-faq-answer">Yes. When you check out, choose "Schedule the email" and pick the date. We hold the gift email and send it on the morning you choose — so it arrives right when the moment matters.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="lg-faq-item">
        <summary>Can I print something to hand them?</summary>
        <p class="lg-faq-answer">Yes — every gift purchase comes with a beautifully designed printable PDF certificate, emailed to <em>you</em> the moment your purchase clears. You can fold it into a card, wrap it, or hand it over in person at the shower — regardless of when (or whether) we email the recipient.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="lg-faq-item">
        <summary>What if they don't want it / don't redeem?</summary>
        <p class="lg-faq-answer">Nothing bad happens. The gift code stays valid as long as you'd like — gift codes don't expire. And nobody is charged anything more, ever, unless the recipient personally redeems and adds their own card after the gift year. There's no awkward auto-renewal landing on you.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="lg-faq-item">
        <summary>What happens after the first year?</summary>
        <p class="lg-faq-answer">After the gift year, the recipient adds their own card to continue at $49.99/year (about $4.17/month). If they choose not to, no one is charged — the book goes private and the domain stays registered through its registration year. They can re-activate any time later.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="lg-faq-item">
        <summary>Can I give more than one?</summary>
        <p class="lg-faq-answer">Of course — many people gift one to each new baby in their family. Each gift is its own code, redeemable for one .com and one book.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

